Task Title: Set up task management system

User Story: As a team member, I want to have access to a task management system that allows me to track my progress and collaborate with others, so that I can contribute effectively to the project.

Description: This task involves setting up a task management system that enables team members to create, assign, and prioritize tasks, as well as track their progress and completion. The system should also allow team members to collaborate and communicate with each other within the system, such as by leaving comments or sharing files, to ensure that everyone is on the same page and working towards the same goals. The acceptance criteria for this task are:
The task management system is set up and accessible to all team members.
Team members are able to create, assign, and prioritize tasks within the system.
The system allows team members to track the progress and completion of tasks.
Team members are able to collaborate and communicate with each other within the system.
The system is user-friendly and intuitive to use.
There are no dependencies for this task.

Effort Estimate: 6 hours

Assigned To: Chris

Priority: High

Status: In progress

Tests:
1. Verify that all team members can access the task management system.
2. Create a task and assign it to another team member. Verify that the task shows up in the other team member's task list.
3. Prioritize a task and verify that it is correctly sorted in the task list.
4. Update the progress of a task and verify that it is reflected in the task management system.
5. Add a comment to a task and verify that it appears in the task details.

Notes: Please ensure that the task management system is easily accessible and can be used by all team members.

